From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: indigoidk <indigoidk@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Thu, 9 Jul 2026 14:25:10 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 02/14] mb87030: no deferred disconnect outside selection

Commit b50b19b459 ("mb87030: Fix some timings") replaced the immediate
initiator bus-free disconnect check - which exempted the Selection states -
with a state-blind 10 ms auto-disconnect timer, armed whenever step() observes
(BSY|SEL)==0 while SSTS_INIT_CONNECTED is set, and fired regardless of state.
Two problems:

1. After a completed command the target releases BSY while SSTS_INIT_CONNECTED
   is still set. A polled controller - the HP 9000/300 boot ROM (98265A card;
   INTS/SSTS/PSNS reads do not step the SPC) - previously got the disconnect
   flagged at its first stepping access; now that access only arms a 10 ms
   timer. The ROM's post-command wait is far shorter than 10 ms, so every
   present target is treated as faulty and retried on a seconds-long backoff;
   the bus scan finds no usable device and the machine drops into "System
   Search Mode". Regressed hp9k330/hp9k340/hp9k360/hp9k370 SCSI boot between
   0.284 and 0.285.

2. On the non-arbitrating selection path SSTS_INIT_CONNECTED is set in
   SelectionAssertID before SEL is asserted, so the timer can be armed
   mid-selection and fire during SelectionWaitBSY: the forced disconnect
   cancels the TC-programmed selection timeout (update_state(Idle) resets
   m_timer) and reports INTS_DISCONNECTED where the datasheet requires the
   Select command to terminate with the Time Out interrupt.

Restore the prompt disconnect, with the exemption widened from the three
Selection states to the whole arbitration/selection execution window, and made
aware of the deferred-transition WaitNewState mechanism from b50b19b459 (while
a delayed transition is pending the effective state lives in m_delay_state).
The wider exemption also covers the case the 10 ms timer presumably existed
for: a Select issued while SSTS_INIT_CONNECTED is still set from the previous
nexus is no longer killed by the stale-connection disconnect. All other
b50b19b459 changes are kept; the now-unused bus-free timer is removed.

Tested: hp9k360 + 98265A boots OpenBSD 2.2 from CD-ROM to the installer with
disk and CD detected (pristine finds no SCSI devices), and the installer writes
through to the disk image. Static analysis found no luna regression: the
restored condition is a strict subset of the pre-b50b19b459 behavior luna ran
on, and the disconnect only fires on genuine guest-initiated bus-free - a
luna88k SCSI smoke-test is the suggested maintainer check.

This change was developed with AI assistance (Anthropic Claude, Fable 5, model
claude-fable-5) for root-cause analysis, drafting, and multi-model review
orchestration; all behavior was verified by live emulator runs as described.
---
 src/devices/machine/mb87030.cpp | 39 +++++++++++++++++++--------------
 src/devices/machine/mb87030.h   |  2 --
 2 files changed, 22 insertions(+), 19 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/devices/machine/mb87030.cpp b/src/devices/machine/mb87030.cpp
index 2aa6a6dd60d..c9f755c926a 100644
--- a/src/devices/machine/mb87030.cpp
+++ b/src/devices/machine/mb87030.cpp
@@ -215,16 +215,6 @@ TIMER_CALLBACK_MEMBER(mb87030_device::delay_timeout)
 	step(false);
 }
 
-TIMER_CALLBACK_MEMBER(mb87030_device::bus_free_timeout)
-{
-	if(!(m_ssts & SSTS_INIT_CONNECTED))
-		return;
-
-	LOG("SCSI disconnect\n");
-	scsi_disconnect();
-	scsi_set_ctrl(0, S_ALL);
-}
-
 void mb87030_device::scsi_command_complete()
 {
 	LOG("%s\n", __FUNCTION__);
@@ -300,12 +290,6 @@ void mb87030_device::step(bool timeout)
 			timeout ? " timeout" : "", data,
 					ctrl, m_tc);
 
-	if ((ctrl & (S_BSY|S_SEL)) == 0) {
-		if ((m_ssts & SSTS_INIT_CONNECTED) && m_bus_free_timer->remaining() == attotime::never)
-			m_bus_free_timer->adjust(attotime::from_msec(10));
-	} else
-		m_bus_free_timer->adjust(attotime::never);
-
 	if ((m_sctl & SCTL_RESET_AND_DISABLE) && m_state != State::Idle) {
 		scsi_set_ctrl(0, S_ALL);
 		m_ssts &= ~SSTS_SPC_BUSY;
@@ -314,6 +298,28 @@ void mb87030_device::step(bool timeout)
 		return;
 	}
 
+	// Bus-free (disconnect) monitoring: when the initiator is connected and
+	// the bus is observed free, flag the disconnect right away.  This must
+	// not trigger while the SPC itself is executing arbitration/selection:
+	// the bus is legitimately free at several points of those sequences, and
+	// a Select command that gets no BSY response must terminate through the
+	// TC-programmed selection timeout (INTS_SPC_TIMEOUT), not through a
+	// disconnect.  m_state parks in WaitNewState while a delayed transition
+	// is pending, so use the effective target state for the check.
+	const State live_state = (m_state == State::WaitNewState) ? m_delay_state : m_state;
+	const bool executing_selection =
+		live_state == State::ArbitrationWaitBusFree || live_state == State::ArbitrationAssertBSY ||
+		live_state == State::ArbitrationWait || live_state == State::ArbitrationAssertSEL ||
+		live_state == State::SelectionWaitBusFree || live_state == State::SelectionAssertID ||
+		live_state == State::SelectionAssertSEL || live_state == State::SelectionWaitBSY ||
+		live_state == State::Selection;
+
+	if ((ctrl & (S_BSY|S_SEL)) == 0 && (m_ssts & SSTS_INIT_CONNECTED) && !executing_selection) {
+		LOG("SCSI disconnect\n");
+		scsi_disconnect();
+		scsi_set_ctrl(0, S_ALL);
+	}
+
 	switch (m_state) {
 	case State::Idle:
 		if (ctrl == 0 && (m_pctl & PCTL_BUS_FREE_IE))
@@ -521,7 +527,6 @@ void mb87030_device::device_start()
 {
 	m_timer = timer_alloc(FUNC(mb87030_device::timeout), this);
 	m_delay_timer = timer_alloc(FUNC(mb87030_device::delay_timeout), this);
-	m_bus_free_timer = timer_alloc(FUNC(mb87030_device::bus_free_timeout), this);
 
 	save_item(NAME(m_bdid));
 	save_item(NAME(m_sctl));
diff --git a/src/devices/machine/mb87030.h b/src/devices/machine/mb87030.h
index 3eeb5457dec..85c1960facb 100644
--- a/src/devices/machine/mb87030.h
+++ b/src/devices/machine/mb87030.h
@@ -142,7 +142,6 @@ private:
 
 	emu_timer *m_timer;
 	emu_timer *m_delay_timer;
-	emu_timer *m_bus_free_timer;
 
 	enum class State: uint8_t {
 		Idle,
@@ -183,7 +182,6 @@ private:
 
 	TIMER_CALLBACK_MEMBER(delay_timeout);
 	TIMER_CALLBACK_MEMBER(timeout);
-	TIMER_CALLBACK_MEMBER(bus_free_timeout);
 
 	// registers
 	uint8_t m_bdid;
